[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating library setup needs**\n\nI need to compare version 5.0.0 with Netty 4.2.1, particularly focusing on native arguments. There seems to be a setup question regarding the library issue that goes beyond the usual scaffold. The current build includes runtime arguments for 5.0.0, yet for 5.0.1 with likely Netty 4.2.2, similar system properties are required. I need to determine whether additional setup is necessary for effective test coverage, specifically regarding the native image verification.\n\n**Researching native runtime issues**\n\nIt seems the scaffold generated for the native runtime isn’t typical, so I'll need to check the documentation. I'm considering the Vert.x Web Client, which usually works with Vert.x and either local or remote HTTP endpoints, but no Docker unless I'm testing against an HTTP server. The option for OAuth2 is unnecessary for core coverage. \n\nThere's a failure in the `ClientMultipartFormUpload.writeQueueFull` method at runtime, possibly due to unsafe access in Netty. In the existing setup for 5.0.0, it seems explicit unsafe access is needed. I’ll have to make sure that the agent guidance includes the necessary runtime arguments in the build.gradle file for version 5.0.1 as well.\n\n**Inspecting resolved artifact**\n\nI need to look into the resolved artifact and consider inspecting the jar classes to find any optional features. I think I could use the command `jar tf`, but, considering my options, it might not be necessary after all. It’s probably best to evaluate if doing so will provide any insights or if I can gather the needed information through other means. I want to ensure I'm efficient with my checks!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09e63b6d8e46d955016a3eba6e99c88190a28d8ee72e259c39\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPrp5zJNbmxE1GhZaCqLYLcfF6JEkB5o05b1WYwQY3Y9pMXBwrByzeqi